notesStmt.note: Title from title page (p. 1); spine title Variationsrechnung.

msContents.summary: Notes by a student from the lectures of Karl Weierstrass on the calculus of variations, in 18 chapters.

supportDesc.extent: 204 leaves : 267 x 196 (268 x 156) mm. bound to 252 x 226 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i + 204 + i leaves; [1-2], 3-405, [406-408]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in cursive script, by a single hand (probably not any of the hands in LJS 206).

decoDesc.decoNote: Occasional small mathematical diagrams in the text (p. 58, 77, 87, 88, 142, 155, 252, 270, 288, 298, 331, 340).

binding.p: Quarter cloth over marbled boards, with spine title Weierstrass, Variationsrechnung (matches the binding of LJS 206).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Archibald Lamont Daniels (American graduate student in mathematics at Göttingen and Berlin who later taught mathematics at the University of Vermont; same binding as LJS 206, which has inscription A. L. Daniels, Berlin-Göttingen, 1879-1883, 49 Mansfield Ave., Burlington, Vt., 1910, on front flyleaf).
Formerly owned by Sydney Ross, professor of chemistry, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, New York (bookplate, inside upper cover).
Appears in 19th Century Shop's cat. 39, p. 23.
Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 38.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2013.
